Troubleshooting Tips
YAML parsing errors:

Check indentation (use spaces, not tabs)
Validate YAML syntax with python3 -c "import yaml; yaml.safe_load(open('file.yaml'))"
Profile not switching:

Verify profile file exists in config/profiles/
Check file permissions: ls -la config/profiles/
Ensure profile name matches filename (without .yaml)
Enforcement not working:

Verify active profile is set: curl http://localhost:8080/status
Check request data format matches expected fields
Review server logs for error messages
Port already in use:

Change port in api_gateway.py: run_server(port=8081)
Or kill existing process: sudo lsof -ti:8080 | xargs kill -9
Conclusion
You've successfully built a multi-profile policy gate system that:

Manages multiple industry-specific compliance profiles (Healthcare/HIPAA, Finance/PCI-DSS, Retail)
Dynamically switches between policy configurations without restart
Enforces different rule sets based on active profile
Provides API-based policy enforcement for integration
This pattern is critical for DevOps engineers managing multi-tenant systems, SaaS platforms serving different industries, or organizations with varying compliance requirements. The ability to switch policies dynamically enables a single system to serve multiple regulatory contexts, reducing infrastructure complexity while maintaining compliance.

